Re-project MET Nordic Data

Source: R/metnordic_reproject.R
metnordic_reproject.Rd

Takes in MET Nordic .nc files as created by metnordic_merge() and re-projects them to desired projection.

Usage

metnordic_reproject(filepath, outfile, projstring = NULL)

Arguments

filepath

path to .nc file to be reprojected

outfile

filepath of .nc file to be created. (if the same file path is used, .nc file will be overwritten)

projstring

desired projection in proj4 format. By default, UTM33N will be used.

Value

Filepath to re-projected file

Details

NOTE: currently only the following projstring has been tested:

projstring <- "+proj=utm +zone=33 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs +type=crs"

See also

metnordic_merge_daily() cwatm_convert_nc()

Author

Moritz Shore
